## CACHING — REDIS ONLY, NO SIGNALR
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

IMPORTANT: There is NO SignalR. Do not reference it anywhere.

Cache-aside with Redis. TTL = 30 seconds (CacheTtlSeconds from config).

Cache keys:
  "flagly:flags:{projectId}:{environmentApiKey}" → JSON flag list
  "flagly:project:{projectSlug}" → project + environments metadata

IFlagCacheService:
  Task<List<FeatureFlagDto>?> GetFlagsAsync(string cacheKey);
  Task SetFlagsAsync(string cacheKey, List<FeatureFlagDto> flags, TimeSpan ttl);
  Task InvalidateAsync(string cacheKey);
  Task InvalidateByProjectIdAsync(Guid projectId);

RedisFlagCacheService:
- IConnectionMultiplexer via DI
- System.Text.Json serialization
- On Redis failure: catch, Serilog.Log.Warning, return null
- InvalidateByProjectIdAsync: SCAN "flagly:flags:{projectId}:*" → delete batch

On any flag/targeting/group change:
1. Save to DB
2. InvalidateByProjectIdAsync(projectId)
3. SDK re-fetches on next poll (≤30s)

