## SDK (Flagly.SDK — classlib)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

FlaglyOptions:
  string ServerUrl
  string ApiKey
  string AppName
  int PollingIntervalSeconds = 30
  bool SendMetrics = true
  bool DefaultWhenUnavailable = false

FlaglyContext:
  string? UserId
  string? UserEmail
  string? SessionId
  Dictionary<string, string> Properties = new()

IFlaglyService:
  bool IsEnabled(string flagName);
  bool IsEnabled(string flagName, string userId);
  bool IsEnabled(string flagName, FlaglyContext context);
  Task RefreshAsync(CancellationToken ct = default);

Usage:
  if (flagly.IsEnabled("awesome-feature")) { }
  if (flagly.IsEnabled("awesome-feature", currentUser.Id)) { }
  var ctx = new FlaglyContext { UserId = "u1", UserEmail = "u@co.com" };
  if (flagly.IsEnabled("awesome-feature", ctx)) { }

SDK internals:
- FlaglyBackgroundService : BackgroundService
  Startup + poll every PollingIntervalSeconds:
    GET /api/client/features → store in ConcurrentDictionary<string, FeatureFlagDto>
  On failure: log warning, keep stale cache
- IsEnabled() is synchronous, zero latency — reads ConcurrentDictionary only.
  NEVER make HTTP calls inside IsEnabled().
- When IsEnabled(flagName, userId) called: build FlaglyContext { UserId = userId }
- Auto-read userId from IHttpContextAccessor if registered (optional)
- Metrics: ConcurrentQueue buffer → flush every 10s via POST /api/client/metrics
- On flag not found: return DefaultWhenUnavailable

Registration:
  builder.Services.AddFlaglySdk(options => {
      options.ServerUrl = config["Flagly:ServerUrl"];
      options.ApiKey = config["Flagly:ApiKey"];
      options.AppName = "my-app";
  });

